verbose_text: Moreover, the endogenous phytohormone and MeJA levels in the test plants were significantly increased by the higher temperature (25degreesC for the phytohormone level; 20degreesC for the MeJA level) and longer photoperiod [14 h, except for abscisic acid (ABA), which had the highest level at 8 h] conditions and were decreased by the lowest test temperature (15degreesC) and shorter photoperiod (8 h, except for ABA) conditions.
